# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — AGENTS.md

This file is read by every agent before starting work on this project. It captures **project-specific overrides** to the global agent definitions in `~/.claude/agents/`. Most projects have very few overrides; defer to the global definitions unless this project has a genuine reason to differ.

## Global agents in use

- **`dev`** — implementation, makes failing tests pass
- **`qa`** — writes failing tests from acceptance criteria
- **`pr-reviewer`** — reviews PRs against checklist
- **`gsd-*`** family — phase planning, research, verification, debugging

See `~/.claude/agents/*.md` for global role definitions and `docs/architecture-overview.md` (in the agentic-workforce-template repo) for how they compose.

